<paragraph id="732E7721FFCDFFCEFEAA23A0DE07FD7A" blockId="26.[264,1327,283,1070]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCDFFCEFEAA23A0DBA5FD51" bold="true" box="[312,427,683,709]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Variation</emphasis>
. The only variations noted have been those of the intensity of the yellow color of the tomentum and in the color of the mid and hind tibiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFCDFFCEFEAA23F0D9C2FCF2" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFCDFFCEFEAA23F0D9C2FCF2" blockId="26.[264,1327,283,1070]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCDFFCEFEAA23F0DBB2FC81" bold="true" box="[312,444,763,789]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species appears to be much like 
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFCDFFCEFC1A23F7D9F8FC81" box="[904,1014,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCDFFCEFC1A23F7D9F8FC81" box="[904,1014,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">G. stenos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5AD61648FFCDFFCEFB9423F7DE6CFC82" box="[1030,1122,764,790]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The two may be separated not only by the differences in the male and female genitalia but also by the much lighter yellow color of the tomentum in 
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCDFFCEFD4C2247D964FCF1" box="[734,874,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFCDFFCEFD4C2247D96BFCF1" box="[734,869,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cressoni" status="sp. nov.">G. cressoni</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5AD61648FFCDFFCEFCE32247D9C2FCF2" box="[881,972,844,870]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFCDFFCEFEAA2278D9FDFC1A" box="[312,1011,883,910]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFCDFFCEFEAA2278D9FDFC1A" blockId="26.[264,1327,283,1070]" box="[312,1011,883,910]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCDFFCEFEAA2278DB9AFC19" bold="true" box="[312,404,883,909]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Biology</emphasis>
. Immature stages and flower preferences unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
